# Read data
url.d <- 'https://ourworldindata.org/wp-content/uploads/datamaps/AgeOfDemocracies2007/AgeOfDemocracies2007.csv'
df.democracies <- read_csv(url.d, col_types = 'ci') 
## Warning: 1 parsing failure.
## row # A tibble: 1 x 5 col     row           col   expected actual expected   <int>         <chr>      <chr>  <chr> actual 1    61 Democduration an integer  #REF! file # ... with 1 more variables: file <chr>
summary(df.democracies)

# Read map
classes = 5
colors = "Blues"

url <- "http://www.naturalearthdata.com/http//www.naturalearthdata.com/download/50m/cultural/ne_50m_admin_0_countries.zip"
tmp <- tempdir()
file <- basename(url)
download.file(url, file)
unzip(file, exdir = tmp)

countries <- readOGR(dsn = tmp, 
                     layer = "ne_50m_admin_0_countries", 
                     encoding = "UTF-8",
                     verbose = FALSE)

leafmap <- merge(countries, 
                 df.democracies, 
                 by.x = "ISO_A3", 
                 by.y = "ISO",                    
                 sort = FALSE)
leafmap <- leafmap[!is.na(leafmap@data$Democduration) ,]

popup_dat <- paste0("<strong>County: </strong>", 
                    leafmap$NAME, 
                    "<br><strong>Value: </strong>", 
                    leafmap$Democduration)

pal <- colorBin(
  palette = "BuPu",
  domain = leafmap$Democduration, 9, pretty=FALSE)

leaflet(data = leafmap) %>%
  addProviderTiles("MapBox", options = providerTileOptions(
    id = "mapbox.light",
    accessToken = Sys.getenv('MAPBOX_ACCESS_TOKEN'))) %>% 
  setView(0, 0, zoom = 2) %>%
  addPolygons(fillColor = ~pal(leafmap[['Democduration']]), 
              fillOpacity = 0.8, 
              smoothFactor = 0.1, 
              color = "white",
              weight = 0.5,
              popup = popup_dat)
